### remote-fastboot
This this fastboot proxy for updating usb-connected devices remotely.

Native fastboot can interract with devices thru usb and tcp. If device supports
only usb interface than remote-fastboot may be used to update that device over network.
remote-fastboot runs tcp server and emulate tcp-capable device while translating all
commands to usb channel

## Local test
./remote-fastboot -l :5444
./fastboot -s tcp:127.0.0.1:5444 flash system system.img

## Command-line options:
-l - host and port to listen to
-s - device serial number (if several devices are connected simulaneously)
-c - check if device is descovrable before starting the server

## Dependencies:
libusb-1.0